message.content:
Chihuahua:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Wide variety including fawn, black, white, chocolate, cream, and combinations; often solid or with light markings  
-Coat Length and Texture: Two coat types—smooth (short, glossy, close-lying) and long (soft, fine, slightly flowing)  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Short, slightly pointed muzzle; apple-shaped, rounded skull  
-Ear Type and Position: Large, erect, set at outer edges of skull, wide base tapering to point  
-Eye Shape and Size: Large, round, expressive, slightly protruding eyes  
-Body Proportions and Build: Very small, compact, slightly longer than tall, fine boned with narrow chest  
-Tail Shape and Length: Moderately long, sickle-shaped or curved over back or to side  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Short, slender legs; small, oval paws with compact toes

Japanese Spaniel:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: White base with black and tan patches, especially on ears and face  
-Coat Length and Texture: Medium to long, silky, fine texture  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Very short muzzle, broad and flat face  
-Ear Type and Position: Large, feathered, pendant ears set high and wide apart  
-Eye Shape and Size: Large, round, dark eyes with prominent expression  
-Body Proportions and Build: Small, compact, slightly rounded body and ribcage  
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, plumed tail curled over the back  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Short legs with feathered hair and compact paws

Maltese_dog:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Pure white, no markings  
-Coat Length and Texture: Long, flowing, silky, straight coat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Short muzzle, slightly rounded skull  
-Ear Type and Position: Drop ears, covered with long hair, placed moderately low  
-Eye Shape and Size: Large, dark, round eyes, expressive  
-Body Proportions and Build: Small, compact, fine-boned, balanced proportions  
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, heavily plumed, carried gracefully over back  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Straight, short legs with small, compact, rounded paws

Pekinese:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Various colors including gold, red, sable, black, and white; often solid or with subtle shading  
-Coat Length and Texture: Long, abundant, dense double coat; coarse and straight outer coat with a woolly undercoat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Very short, flat muzzle; broad, flat face with pronounced wrinkles  
-Ear Type and Position: Drop ears, heavily feathered, set moderately high and close to head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Large, dark, prominent, and round eyes set wide apart  
-Body Proportions and Build: Compact, low-slung, sturdy body with a broad chest and substantial bone structure  
-Tail Shape and Length: High-set, heavily plumed tail carried over the back  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Short, straight legs with well-padded, compact paws

Shih-Tzu:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Wide variety including white, black, brown, gold, often multi-colored or brindle  
-Coat Length and Texture: Long, flowing, dense double coat, silky texture  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Very short muzzle; rounded, flat face with distinct stop  
-Ear Type and Position: Large, heavily furred, pendant ears set at eye level  
-Eye Shape and Size: Large, round, dark eyes, prominent and expressive  
-Body Proportions and Build: Small, sturdy, compact body with broad chest  
-Tail Shape and Length: Heavily plumed tail, arched and carried over the back  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Short legs; round, compact paws with feathering

Blenheim Spaniel:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Rich chestnut red markings on pearly white background, with distinct symmetrical blaze on face  
-Coat Length and Texture: Medium length, silky and slightly wavy coat with feathering on ears, chest, legs, and tail  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Moderate length muzzle, slightly rounded skull with well-defined stop  
-Ear Type and Position: Long, low-set, pendant ears heavily feathered  
-Eye Shape and Size: Large, dark, round eyes with gentle expression  
-Body Proportions and Build: Compact, well-balanced body with moderate chest depth  
-Tail Shape and Length: Moderately long tail, carried level or slightly raised, well feathered  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Straight, moderately long legs with well-feathered, compact, round paws

Papillon:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Predominantly white with patches of black, brown, or sable, especially on ears and face  
-Coat Length and Texture: Long, fine, silky, and flowing coat with feathering on ears, chest, legs, and tail  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Medium-length muzzle; slightly rounded skull with a tapered face  
-Ear Type and Position: Large, butterfly-shaped, erect ears set high on the head with abundant fringe  
-Eye Shape and Size: Dark, round to slightly oval eyes, medium size, expressive  
-Body Proportions and Build: Small, fine-boned, elegant and balanced body with a slightly rounded ribcage  
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, plumed tail carried high and arched over the back  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Moderately long legs with feathered, small, oval paws

Toy Terrier:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Usually black and tan or all black, occasionally other dark colors  
-Coat Length and Texture: Short, smooth, and shiny coat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Moderately long, slender muzzle with a narrow face  
-Ear Type and Position: Large, pointed, erect ears set high on the head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Almond-shaped, medium-sized dark eyes  
-Body Proportions and Build: Small, slender, and fine-boned body with a well-defined chest  
-Tail Shape and Length: Thin, moderately long tail, often carried straight or slightly curved  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Long, thin legs relative to body size; small, delicate paws

Rhodesian Ridgeback:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Light wheaten to red wheaten, uniform coloring; distinctive dorsal ridge of hair growing in opposite direction along spine
-Coat Length and Texture: Short, dense, sleek and glossy coat
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Long, broad muzzle; strong and well-defined stop
-Ear Type and Position: Medium-sized, rounded at tips; set high and carried close to head
-Eye Shape and Size: Round to almond-shaped eyes; medium size; amber to brown color
-Body Proportions and Build: Muscular, athletic, balanced body; deep chest and strong loin
-Tail Shape and Length: Thick at base, tapering to tip; carried low or slightly curved upward
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Long, straight legs; tight, round paws with well-arched toes

Afghan_hound:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Varied colors, often solid or with subtle shading; no distinct pattern
-Coat Length and Texture: Very long, fine, silky, flowing coat
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Long, narrow muzzle; chiseled, refined face
-Ear Type and Position: Long, pendant ears heavily feathered, set low and back
-Eye Shape and Size: Almond-shaped eyes, dark and expressive
-Body Proportions and Build: Tall, lean, and elegant with a deep chest and tucked-up abdomen
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, thin tail with a distinctive ring or curl at the end
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Long, slender legs with well-feathered feet and compact paws

Basset:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Tricolor (brown, black, white) or bicolor combinations, often with large patches
-Coat Length and Texture: Short, smooth, dense coat
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Long, broad muzzle with pronounced stop; loose skin around face
-Ear Type and Position: Very long, pendant ears hanging close to cheeks, set low on head
-Eye Shape and Size: Large, oval, droopy eyes often with visible lower eyelids
-Body Proportions and Build: Long, low-slung body with deep chest and pronounced ribcage
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium length, tapered tail carried upright but not curled
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Very short, sturdy legs with large, rounded paws and thick pads

Beagle:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Tri-color (black, white, tan) or bicolor; distinctive white-tipped tail
-Coat Length and Texture: Short, dense, smooth coat
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Medium-length muzzle; square, straight profile
-Ear Type and Position: Broad, long, floppy ears set low on head
-Eye Shape and Size: Large, round to slightly oval eyes; warm brown color
-Body Proportions and Build: Compact, muscular body; slightly longer than tall
-Tail Shape and Length: Moderately long, straight tail; carried high with white tip
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Medium-length legs; sturdy, round paws

Bloodhound:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Typically black and tan, liver and tan, or red; solid colors with minimal markings  
-Coat Length and Texture: Short, dense, and coarse coat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Very long, broad muzzle with deep wrinkles and loose skin around face  
-Ear Type and Position: Exceptionally long, thick, pendulous ears set low on head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Deep-set, droopy eyes with heavy eyelids, generally brown or hazel  
-Body Proportions and Build: Large, muscular, and heavy-boned body with loose skin forming pronounced folds  
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, tapering tail carried low or slightly curved  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Long, sturdy legs with large, well-padded paws and thick skin

Bluetick:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Blue mottled and ticked pattern on white background, black spots on head and body
-Coat Length and Texture: Short, dense, smooth coat with glossy appearance
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Medium-length muzzle, broad skull, slightly domed forehead
-Ear Type and Position: Long, pendant ears set moderately high and hanging close to head
-Eye Shape and Size: Almond-shaped, medium-sized, hazel to brown eyes
-Body Proportions and Build: Medium-large, muscular and athletic build with deep chest
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium length, tapered, usually held level or slightly upward
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Long legs with strong bone structure, compact, well-arched paws

black-and-tan_coonhound:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Black body with distinct rich tan markings on muzzle, chest, legs, and above eyes
-Coat Length and Texture: Short, dense, and smooth coat
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Long, straight muzzle with a pronounced stop
-Ear Type and Position: Very long, wide, rounded pendant ears set low and hanging close to cheeks
-Eye Shape and Size: Medium-sized, almond-shaped eyes, usually brown or hazel
-Body Proportions and Build: Large, muscular, and athletic build with deep chest and strong neck
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, tapering tail usually carried high with slight curve
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Long, powerful legs with large, well-padded, compact paws

Walker Hound:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Tricolor (black saddle, white body, tan markings on face and legs)  
-Coat Length and Texture: Short, dense, smooth coat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Medium-length muzzle, straight and square-shaped face  
-Ear Type and Position: Long, wide, pendant ears set low on head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Almond-shaped, medium-sized eyes, typically brown  
-Body Proportions and Build: Muscular, lean body with deep chest and strong neck  
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium length, tapered tail carried level or slightly curved  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Long legs with compact, well-padded paws

English Foxhound:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Tri-color (black, white, tan) or sometimes lemon and white; large, defined patches  
-Coat Length and Texture: Short, dense, hard coat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Long, straight muzzle; elongated head shape  
-Ear Type and Position: Long, broad, low-set ears hanging close to cheeks  
-Eye Shape and Size: Medium-sized, almond-shaped eyes, usually brown or hazel  
-Body Proportions and Build: Lean, muscular, medium-large frame; deep chest and strong legs  
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium length, straight or slightly curved, tapering to a point  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Long, strong legs with compact, well-arched paws

Redbone:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Solid deep reddish-brown color uniformly distributed  
-Coat Length and Texture: Short, smooth, and glossy coat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Medium-length muzzle; broad, slightly tapered face  
-Ear Type and Position: Medium-sized, pendant ears set moderately high, lying close to head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Medium-sized, almond-shaped eyes; warm brown color  
-Body Proportions and Build: Muscular, well-proportioned, athletic build with deep chest  
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium length, tapering, carried straight or slightly curved  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Strong, moderately long legs with compact, round paws

Borzoi:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Often white, cream, tan, or gray, sometimes with brindle or sable markings  
-Coat Length and Texture: Long, wavy or silky, flowing coat with feathering on legs and tail  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Very long, narrow, and tapering muzzle; slightly convex skull profile  
-Ear Type and Position: Small, thin, set high, typically carried back against the neck when relaxed  
-Eye Shape and Size: Almond-shaped, medium-sized eyes giving a keen expression  
-Body Proportions and Build: Tall, slender, and graceful with deep chest and narrow waist  
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, curved, and feathered, often carried low or in a gentle upward curve  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Long, slender legs with compact, well-arched paws

Irish Wolfhound:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Typically gray, brindle, red, black, or wheaten; solid and often grizzled appearance  
-Coat Length and Texture: Rough, coarse, wiry, and shaggy coat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Very long muzzle; narrow and elongated face with a somewhat rectangular shape  
-Ear Type and Position: Small to medium size, folded back close to the head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Small to medium-sized, deep-set, dark eyes  
-Body Proportions and Build: Very tall and large size; lean but muscular with a deep chest and long neck  
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, heavy, slightly curved tail often carried low  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Very long legs; large, round, and strong paws with thick pads

Italian Greyhound:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Solid colors common; includes blue, fawn, black, white, and brindle  
-Coat Length and Texture: Very short, fine, smooth, and glossy coat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Long, narrow muzzle; refined and delicate face structure  
-Ear Type and Position: Small, rose-shaped ears set high and folded back  
-Eye Shape and Size: Almond-shaped, medium-sized dark eyes  
-Body Proportions and Build: Slender, lightweight, graceful body with deep chest and tucked-up abdomen  
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, thin tail, tapered and carried low with slight curve  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Long, slender legs; small, delicate oval paws with well-arched toes

Whippet:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Wide variety including solid, brindle, and pied patterns
-Coat Length and Texture: Short, smooth, fine coat
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Long, narrow muzzle; streamlined face
-Ear Type and Position: Small, rose-shaped ears set high and folded back
-Eye Shape and Size: Medium, almond-shaped eyes
-Body Proportions and Build: Lean, slender, aerodynamic build; deep chest with narrow waist
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, tapered tail carried low
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Long, slim legs with small, compact paws

Ibizan Hound:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Predominantly solid colors, usually red or white, sometimes mixed red and white  
-Coat Length and Texture: Short and smooth or rough and wiry coat variants  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Long, slender muzzle; narrow, elongated face  
-Ear Type and Position: Large, upright, pointed ears set high on the head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Almond-shaped eyes, medium size, amber or brown color  
-Body Proportions and Build: Tall, lean, and athletic build with deep chest and narrow waist  
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, tapering tail, carried low with slight curve  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Very long legs with narrow, elongated paws

Norwegian_elkhound:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Dense gray with black-tipped guard hairs, lighter undercoat; consistent solid coloration  
-Coat Length and Texture: Medium-length, thick, coarse double coat with soft undercoat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Medium-length muzzle; broad, wedge-shaped face  
-Ear Type and Position: Medium-sized, erect, triangular ears set high on head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Medium-sized, dark brown, almond-shaped eyes  
-Body Proportions and Build: Compact, sturdy, square-shaped body with deep chest  
-Tail Shape and Length: Full, bushy tail tightly curled over the back or side  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Medium-length, strong legs with compact, well-padded paws

Otterhound:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Commonly lemon, red, wheaten, or black and tan; often mixed shades, sometimes grizzled  
-Coat Length and Texture: Thick, coarse, rough, and water-resistant double coat; dense undercoat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Long, broad muzzle with pronounced whiskers and pronounced beard  
-Ear Type and Position: Large, rounded, pendant ears hanging close to cheeks, set low on head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Medium-sized, deep-set eyes, often hazel or brown  
-Body Proportions and Build: Large, heavy-boned, muscular body with deep chest and slightly arched neck  
-Tail Shape and Length: Thick at base, tapering to tip, moderately long, carried level or slightly curved  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Moderate length legs with large, webbed paws adapted for swimming

Saluki:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Wide variety including cream, white, tan, black, and combinations; often with feathering on ears and tail
-Coat Length and Texture: Smooth, silky coat with feathering on ears, tail, and sometimes legs
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Long, narrow muzzle; refined and chiseled face
-Ear Type and Position: Long, hanging ears with silky feathering, set low and close to head
-Eye Shape and Size: Large, almond-shaped eyes, dark and expressive
-Body Proportions and Build: Lean, elegant, and aerodynamic body with deep chest and narrow waist
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, curved tail with feathering, tapered toward the end
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Very long, slender legs; small, compact, oval-shaped paws with well-arched toes

Scottish Deerhound:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Typically brindle, blue-gray, fawn, or wheaten; solid color, no distinct markings  
-Coat Length and Texture: Rough, wiry, and shaggy coat; dense and wiry texture  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Long, narrow muzzle; elongated and slightly pointed face  
-Ear Type and Position: Small to medium size, folded back and set high on head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Medium-sized, dark eyes; slightly almond-shaped  
-Body Proportions and Build: Tall, lean, and muscular; deep chest with narrow waist  
-Tail Shape and Length: Long, slightly curved downward tail with a slight feathering  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Very long legs; large, strong, and well-padded paws

Weimaraner:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Uniform silver-gray to mouse-gray, sometimes with faint ticking  
-Coat Length and Texture: Short, sleek, and smooth coat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Long, straight muzzle; chiseled, noble face  
-Ear Type and Position: Long, floppy ears set high, hanging close to head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Almond-shaped eyes, light amber to pale blue-gray  
-Body Proportions and Build: Athletic, lean, moderately large with deep chest and well-muscled frame  
-Tail Shape and Length: Docked tail, straight and held horizontally  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Long, strong legs with compact, well-arched paws

Staffordshire Bull Terrier:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Solid colors or bi-color; common colors include brindle, black, blue, fawn, red, white; often with white markings  
-Coat Length and Texture: Short, smooth, and close-lying coat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Short, broad muzzle; strong jawline; broad head with pronounced cheek muscles  
-Ear Type and Position: Small to medium, rose or half-pricked ears set high on head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Dark, round to almond-shaped eyes; medium size  
-Body Proportions and Build: Compact, muscular, stocky build; deep chest; broad shoulders; well-defined muscles  
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium length, tapering to a point; low set; carried low or horizontal  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Medium-length legs; strong, straight forelegs; compact, round paws with thick pads

American_Staffordshire_terrier:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Solid colors or bi-color; common colors include brindle, black, blue, fawn, and white patches  
-Coat Length and Texture: Short, stiff, glossy coat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Medium-length muzzle; broad and strong face with pronounced cheek muscles  
-Ear Type and Position: Ears are often cropped or naturally rose-shaped; set high on head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Round to almond-shaped eyes; medium size, dark-colored  
-Body Proportions and Build: Muscular, stocky, and well-balanced with a deep chest and broad shoulders  
-Tail Shape and Length: Tapered tail, medium length, carried low  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Medium-length legs; strong, compact, and well-arched paws

Bedlington Terrier:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Typically blue, liver, or sandy; often with tan points on legs and face
-Coat Length and Texture: Curly, dense, woolly coat with a crisp texture
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Narrow, tapering muzzle; distinctive pear-shaped head with a topknot
-Ear Type and Position: Almond-shaped ears, set low and close to head, often with tassels
-Eye Shape and Size: Almond-shaped, small to medium-sized, dark eyes
-Body Proportions and Build: Slender, arched back with a graceful, athletic build
-Tail Shape and Length: Thin, tapering tail, carried low or slightly curved
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Moderate leg length; small, cat-like, well-knuckled paws

Border_terrier:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Grizzle and tan, reddish brown, wheat, or blue and tan  
-Coat Length and Texture: Dense, wiry, harsh outer coat with a soft undercoat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Medium-length muzzle, otter-shaped face with a strong jaw  
-Ear Type and Position: Small, V-shaped ears folding forward close to cheeks  
-Eye Shape and Size: Small to medium, dark, almond-shaped eyes  
-Body Proportions and Build: Compact, muscular, slightly rectangular body with a deep chest  
-Tail Shape and Length: Short, thick tail carried erect but not curled  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Moderate leg length with strong, cat-like, compact paws

Kerry Blue Terrier:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Solid steel blue coat, color deepens with age  
-Coat Length and Texture: Dense, soft, wavy, and curly coat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Moderate-length muzzle, strong jaw, tapered face  
-Ear Type and Position: Small to medium V-shaped ears, folded forward close to head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Dark, almond-shaped eyes, moderately sized  
-Body Proportions and Build: Medium-sized, well-muscled, square-proportioned body  
-Tail Shape and Length: Moderately short, carried erect or slightly curved  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Straight, moderately long legs; small, round, compact paws

Irish Terrier:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Solid rich red or ginger, no markings
-Coat Length and Texture: Dense, wiry, and harsh coat; close-lying
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Long, strong muzzle; rectangular shape
-Ear Type and Position: Small to medium, V-shaped, folding forward close to head
-Eye Shape and Size: Small to medium, dark, almond-shaped eyes
-Body Proportions and Build: Square build, deep chest, well-muscled and athletic
-Tail Shape and Length: Set high, carried erect, usually docked medium length
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Long, straight legs; compact, round paws with tight toes

Norfolk Terrier:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Red, wheaten, black and tan, or grizzle
-Coat Length and Texture: Medium length, wiry and dense coat
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Short, strong muzzle; broad skull with a slight stop
-Ear Type and Position: Small, V-shaped, carried forward close to the cheeks (drop ears)
-Eye Shape and Size: Dark, medium-sized, round eyes
-Body Proportions and Build: Compact, low-set, sturdy body with deep chest
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium length, straight tail, carried upright but not curled
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Short legs; round, firm paws with thick pads

Norwich Terrier:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Red, wheaten, black and tan, or grizzle and tan; solid or slight shading, no distinct markings  
-Coat Length and Texture: Harsh, wiry, dense, and weather-resistant coat; medium length  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Moderately short muzzle; slightly tapered face with strong jaw  
-Ear Type and Position: Erect, pointed, small to medium-sized ears set high on head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Dark, round to oval eyes, medium size, lively expression  
-Body Proportions and Build: Compact, sturdy, square-bodied with deep chest and short back  
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium length, carried gaily but not curled over back, straight or slightly curved  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Short legs, strong bone; small, round, firm paws with thick pads

Yorkshire Terrier:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Steel blue body with rich tan on face, chest, and legs  
-Coat Length and Texture: Long, straight, silky coat often flowing to the ground  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Medium-length muzzle; small, narrow face with a slightly pointed nose  
-Ear Type and Position: Small, V-shaped, erect ears set high on head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Dark, medium-sized, almond-shaped eyes  
-Body Proportions and Build: Small, compact, fine-boned body with a level topline  
-Tail Shape and Length: Traditionally docked short, carried upright or slightly curved  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Short, straight legs with small, neat, rounded paws

Wire-Haired Fox Terrier:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Predominantly white with black and tan markings, especially on head and body  
-Coat Length and Texture: Dense, harsh, wiry coat with close fitting undercoat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Long, strong muzzle; flat skull with a pronounced stop  
-Ear Type and Position: Small to medium, V-shaped, folded forward and close to head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Dark, small to medium, deep-set, and sharp expression  
-Body Proportions and Build: Compact, muscular body with slightly arched neck and deep chest  
-Tail Shape and Length: Moderately short, set high, carried erect  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Straight, moderately long legs; small, round, compact paws

Lakeland Terrier:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Predominantly red, wheaten, black and tan, or blue and tan; solid colors without markings  
-Coat Length and Texture: Harsh, dense, wiry outer coat with a softer undercoat; medium length  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Straight, moderately short muzzle; rectangular face shape with strong jawline  
-Ear Type and Position: V-shaped, folded forward ears set high on head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Small to medium, dark, almond-shaped eyes  
-Body Proportions and Build: Compact, square-shaped body; deep chest with strong, muscular build  
-Tail Shape and Length: Set high, traditionally docked short, carried erect  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Straight, moderately short legs with firm, round paws and thick pads

Sealyham Terrier:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Predominantly white with occasional light tan markings on ears or body  
-Coat Length and Texture: Medium length, dense, wiry, and harsh coat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Short, squared muzzle with prominent beard and bushy eyebrows  
-Ear Type and Position: Small to medium, folded (rose ears), set moderately high  
-Eye Shape and Size: Small to medium, dark, deep-set eyes  
-Body Proportions and Build: Low-slung, sturdy, compact body with a broad chest  
-Tail Shape and Length: Medium length, thick at base, carried erect or slightly curved  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Short legs with strong bone, round paws

Airedale:
-Fur Color and Pattern: Tan and black saddle pattern; black coloration on back and upper sides
-Coat Length and Texture: Medium-length, dense, wiry, and rough coat
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Long, rectangular muzzle with a straight bridge
-Ear Type and Position: V-shaped, folded ears set high on head
-Eye Shape and Size: Small to medium, dark, deep-set eyes
-Body Proportions and Build: Medium-large, sturdy and square build with deep chest
-Tail Shape and Length: Straight tail, carried erect and docked to medium length
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Long, straight legs with compact, round paws

Cairn Terrier:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Cream, wheaten, red, gray, or brindle; often mixed shades  
-Coat Length and Texture: Harsh, weather-resistant, wiry outer coat with soft undercoat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Moderate length muzzle; slightly rounded skull with distinct stop  
-Ear Type and Position: Small, erect, pointed ears set wide apart and high on head  
-Eye Shape and Size: Dark, deep-set, almond-shaped eyes  
-Body Proportions and Build: Compact, sturdy, slightly longer than tall; well-balanced  
-Tail Shape and Length: Short, tapered, carried upright but not curled  
-Leg Length and Paw Characteristics: Short legs; strong, rounded paws with thick pads

Australian Terrier:  
-Fur Color and Pattern: Medium steel blue body with tan head, ears, and legs  
-Coat Length and Texture: Harsh, wiry, short to medium length coat  
-Muzzle Length and Face Shape: Medium-length muzzle; slightly tapered face with a prominent whiskered beard
